  "texts": [
    "RGB-D data have been used to detect heavily occluded and out-of-view targets.",
    "In recent works, this auxiliary modality has achieved 8.5%-31.3% relative improvement in terms of tracking accuracy on corresponding datasets [10,[29][30][31].",
    "Thus, the complementary characteristics of multi-modal data can significantly improve tracking accuracy and robustness.",
    "Lan et al. [32] applied the sparse learning method to RGB-T tracking, thereby removing the cross-modality discrepancy.",
    "Li et al. [11] extended the RGB tracker to the RGB-T domain, achieving promising results."
  ],
